<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-20"><hi rend="italic">June 20,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 400.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the minister’s unnumbered
                            dispatch of the 10th instant, explaining his action in behalf of the
                            Swiss citizen, Robert Beck, I inclose copy of the Department
                                memorandum<note n="a" xml:id="d247fna">Printed, <ref target="#pg_980">page 980</ref>.</note> of the same date in
                            regard to the case, addressed to the Swiss legation at this capital.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>